        "http://docbook.org/xml/5.0/dtd/docbook.dtd">

<chapter xml:id="projectStructure">
    <title>Project structure</title>
    <para>The project is generally splitted into 4 parts
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <emphasis>android</emphasis>: contains the sources of the android application.
                </para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis>app</emphasis>: main application with main class
                        </para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis>storage</emphasis>: DataAccess layer working with
                            <link xlink:href="http://ormlite.com/">ormlite</link>
                        </para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>


            <listitem>
                <para><emphasis>pc</emphasis>: contains the sources of the
                    <link xlink:href="http://download.java.net/jdk8/jfxdocs/index.html">JavaFX8</link>
                    application
                </para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis>app</emphasis>: main class and
                            <link xlink:href="http://download.java.net/jdk8/jfxdocs/index.html">JavaFX8</link>
                            application
                        </para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis>libs</emphasis>: Contains various small libraries that build parts
                            of the application and might be shared in future projects of mine.
                        </para>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para><emphasis>application</emphasis>: Contains launcher and window descriptors for
                                    fast creation of
                                    JavaFX applications.
                                </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para><emphasis>cdi-scope</emphasis>: Contains a custom
                                    <link xlink:href="http://cdi-spec.org/">cdi</link>
                                    scope which can store and destroy bulks/sessions of objects
                                </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para><emphasis>eventsystem</emphasis>: Access to the eventsystem libraries the
                                    application
                                    communicates with. Based on
                                    <link xlink:href="http://code.google.com/p/guava-libraries/">guava</link>
                                    EventBus
                                </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para><emphasis>i18n</emphasis>: Contains some classes for internationalization,
                                    basically
                                    an UTF8 resource bundle.
                                </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para><emphasis>images</emphasis>: Contains a basic image cache based on SoftReferences
                                    which also supports lazy loading.
                                </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para><emphasis>menu</emphasis>: Contains a CDI extension for discovering menu items.
                                    (@MenuItem(menuPath) Annotated classes)
                                    Also supports building of different kinds of menus.
                                </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para><emphasis>persistence</emphasis>: JPA storage via
                                    <link xlink:href="http://hibernate.org/">hibernate</link>
                                    and helper classes for basic transaction management
                                </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para><emphasis>reflection</emphasis>: Reflection utilities, I sadly can't use
                                    "org.reflections:reflections:0.9.9-RC1"
                                    because it destroys hibernate.
                                </para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para><emphasis>scheduler</emphasis>: Contains an Entity Schedule used to schedule
                                    specific events.
                                    A Daemon is used to trigger events based on those schedules
                                </para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
                <para><emphasis>doc</emphasis>: contains this beagle reference documentation
                </para>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </para>
    <section>
        <title>Beagle internal dependency graph</title>
        <para>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="images/dependencygraph.jpg"/>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </para>
    </section>
</chapter>